Author: Yauheni Pervenenka <yauheni.pervenenka@viber.com>
Date:   Mon Jul 6 13:44:23 2026 +0300

    macOS: Release displayLock on early return from displayLayer
    
    When setNeedsDisplayInRect: acquires the QMetalLayer displayLock for
    write and CoreAnimation subsequently calls displayLayer: which returns
    early (e.g. for a non-online screen during sleep/wake), the write lock
    was never released. This permanently blocks deliverUpdateRequest() from
    acquiring a read lock, deadlocking the render thread.
    
    Use qScopeGuard to ensure the lock is released on any early-return path.
    The guard is dismissed on the normal display path where the existing
    deferred QueuedConnection unlock handles it.
    
    Fixes: QTBUG-147933
    Pick-to: 6.12 6.11
    Change-Id: I2545a984ba6f8c0fc4c4a985061e7b0277b965d9
    Reviewed-by: Tor Arne Vestbø <tor.arne.vestbo@qt.io>

